         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] for him who (is self-restrained), lives according to the law</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] (and is careful, fame) increases [SKT] (do not be negligent) in your minds!</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] (one should) not (dwell) with negligence</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] one should not like a (wrong) view</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] [who has] a (completely) right view</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels"><bibl><title corresp="ref:bernhard1965"/><citedRange>127-128</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:levi1912a"/><citedRange>241-245</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:hahn2007"/><citedRange>23-24</citedRange></bibl></note><note type="remarks">Possibly the leaf directly following <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-ioltoch928"/>.</note><note type="remarks">The lines are numbered on the assumption that the fragment is from the same ms. as <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-ioltoch928"/>: a1 may have contained 4.6a; a2 4.6b; a6 4.7b-c; b1 7d-8a. On <ref target="http://idp.bl.uk/database/oo_loader.a4d?pm=IOL%20Toch%20479" type="external">IDP</ref>, recto and verso are reversed.</note><note corresp="#a3" type="philcomment">Uv.4.6c <hi>saṃyatasya hi dharmajīvinaḥ</hi></note><note corresp="#a4" type="philcomment">Uv.4.6d-7a <hi>hy apramattasya yaśo ’bhivardhate // 6 adhicetasi mā pramadyata</hi></note><note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment">Uv.4.8b <hi>pramādena na saṃvaset</hi>, see Dhp.167 (and <bibl><title corresp="ref:norman2004"/><citedRange>26</citedRange></bibl>)</note><note corresp="#b3" type="philcomment">Uv.4.8c <hi>mithyādṛṣṭiṃ na roceta</hi>, see Dhp.167 (and <bibl><title corresp="ref:norman2004"/><citedRange>26</citedRange></bibl>)</note><note corresp="#b4" type="philcomment">Uv.4.9a <hi>samyagdṛṣṭir adhīmātrā</hi></note></p>
         </div>
